      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Staying Married and Paying a Price'' (Op-Ed, Oct. 12) conveys exactly the kind of realistic yet progressive message that Americans need to heed.</p>
        <p>In South Asia, where I come from, forgiving, mending and surviving troublesome relationships is a time-tested practical skill. Many women there are able to empathize deeply with Hillary Rodham Clinton without having to endorse an erring mate or to trade a less-than-ideal life for a worse, unhappy one.</p>
        <p>JALAL ALAMGIR  Boston, Oct. 12, 2000</p>
      </block>
